SIMPLE: stagnant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stagnant
<hw>Stag"nant</hw> <pr>(-n⟦ait⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stagnans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>stagnare</ets>.
See <er>Stagnate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That stagnates; not
flowing; not running in a current or steam; motionless; hence, impure or
foul from want of motion; <as>as, a <ex>stagnant</ex> lake or pond;
<ex>stagnant</ex> blood in the veins.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not active or brisk; dull; <as>as, business is
<ex>stagnant</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That gloomy slumber of the <qex>stagnant</qex> soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For him a <qex>stagnant</qex> life was not worth living.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stagnantly</ent>⟦br⟧
